title: Dropbox Paper
description:
For the last year or so I've been working with some wonderful humans on Paper, a super simple way to quickly share ideas with your team. We're about to start sending out more invites, so make sure you sign up for the beta at dropbox.com/paper.

These days I use Paper constantly to share everything from early ideas and sketches to full design specs (complete with my Sketch files) - getting feedback from my team every step of the way. I really hope you'll enjoy using it too.

A ton of people have been instrumental in shaping Paper, and I specifically wanted to call out Tony, Linda, Nick, Dave, David, and Jeremiah for all the love they poured into the interaction and visual design of this product.

One last thing - you can read more about it on Wired, Engadget, and Fast Company.

title: Low Fidelity Reservation Flow
description: Here is an example of how an interaction prototype usually starts out in a project. A low fidelity version is created to illustrate how the UX may work with a high level interaction concept. After the user's flow is solid we then start to layer more refined motion on top of that while incorporating high fidelity designs. Prototyping with programs like Principle also make it super easy to update these alongside wires efficiently during the UX process.
